==French==

===Etymology===
French sémite, from Semitic Shem, from Late Latin, from Greek SEm, from Hebrew ShEm

===Pronunciation===
'se-"mIt, esp British 'sE-"mIt

===Noun===
# a member of any of a number of peoples of ancient southwestern Asia including the Akkadians, Phoenicians, Hebrews, and Arabs.
# descendant of these peoples.
# a member of a modern people speaking a [[semitic|Semitic]] language.